Thank you for using Nixx ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our voice chat room app, Nixx. By using Nixx, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information when you use Nixx:

a. Personal Information
Account Information: When you create an account, we collect your username, email address, phone number, and password.

Profile Information: You may provide additional information such as a profile picture, bio, or other details.

Payment Information: If you purchase or send coins, we may collect payment details (e.g., credit card information, PayPal account). Note that we do not store full payment details; these are processed by third-party payment processors.

b. Usage Information
Voice Chat Data: We collect audio data when you participate in voice chat rooms.

Transaction Data: We collect information about coin transactions, including sender and receiver details, amounts, and timestamps.

Device Information: We collect device-specific information such as your device model, operating system, IP address, and unique device identifiers.

Log Data: We collect log files that include your activity on the app, such as room creation, joining rooms, and interactions with other users.

c. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We may use cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies to track your activity on the app and improve your experience.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide, maintain, and improve the app's functionality.

To facilitate voice chat rooms and coin transactions.

To verify your identity and prevent fraud.

To communicate with you, including sending updates, security alerts, and support messages.

To analyze usage trends and improve user experience.

To comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms of service.

3. How We Share Your Information
We may share your information in the following circumstances:

With Other Users: Your username and profile information may be visible to other users in the chat rooms. Coin transactions may also be visible to participants in the room.

With Service Providers: We may share information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating the app, processing payments, or analyzing data.

For Legal Reasons: We may disclose information if required by law, to protect our rights, or to comply with a legal process.

Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred to the new owner.

4. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:

Access: Request a copy of the information we hold about you.

Correction: Request corrections to inaccurate or incomplete information.

Deletion: Request deletion of your information, subject to legal obligations.

Opt-Out: Opt out of marketing communications or certain data processing activities.

To exercise these rights, please contact us at support@nixxapp.com.

6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Nixx is not intended for users under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information.

7. International Transfers
Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own, where data protection laws may differ. By using Nixx, you consent to such transfers.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our website and updating the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of Nixx after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.

